{"author":{"id":"4fe3a4b41833d8e56f9aa54c6b0c85961b25ef36f735c736a3283cfbd2adc6db"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1481817836,"nonce":"iht7lkCKHduGU8jmKaUMzSE+54A=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxOTU4NDQwNDI=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1080","origin":"github"},"title":"sra-tools fail download from weird 3 reads per spot issue","message":"It seems that some sequencing centre have uploaded some SRAs that are paired end libraries but for some reason, they decided to indicate there is 3 reads instead of 2.  Example would be  https://trace.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Traces/sra/?run=ERR027434\n\nThe first and THIRD reads are the forward and reverse respectively but the second read (_2) is a no length read between forward and reverse.\n\nSo fastq-dump will dump out SRA_1 and SRA_**3** instead of SRA_1 and SRA_**2** . Hence the discover datasets in \u003coutput\u003e section will fail.  fastq-dump actually indicate that is ignoring _2 because all reads have zero length.","files":null}]}